TextBlock.TextLine: London Abram wean
mij last toyou was on the 21th cuurtt. sence non from you, inclosed a bill for £150
att 2 a hicht for my acctt. on m. ad. Gromen, for which please to procure the needfes
& note accordingly, pray spare mee in yd dranghts, because itt y our advantidge
I hope most all the goods are ready aboaud Findan God send im safe to
arrive I first, before yd. sale be over, m. moens shewd mee yd. letder to dim, le
could not understand itt, I could with you could wiite to dim in frenck. I have neghard
to tell hum the seafure of n°. 10, because I oid exspect that itt I could lave been
ncleased before now, to yd advise did surpuse dny I could wish you could incorridge
the lace trade with hm, for ie is a man I lave a great rispect for is the
no hopen of geking of n. 1o, I could advise you to cleare then laces as best you can
I lave payd no mens yd. cale gart in the 3 packets you read from m. van de
Butt £134„1:8, which proy note accordingy, se pretents yott £5:7„8 fleurish for
yd. hare which you promise to allow for the risico of bringing them in which
pray note accordingl to yd acctt, I have sent for Rotterdam to m. sHartely a
case g. 12 pictures beeng & to be sent you by the mary yaght, I am
parviding more of which langer frepte
London arthur anneslay
In answer to yd of 6 curtt. shall accept yd bill when presented. I shall
also verey suddamby send the needfull acctts & cleare alsogheter to make an end
to that concerre. Inclosed the bill on van Berge acepted t
andenarde Jan B: At
bij den ul van 21 deser bevinde al wederom dillaye: lad niet getwijffele oft
ul soude voor min den nsselse hebben voldaen aen m. Baert. ul leest mij
groote preginditie gedaen met soo daigen uijtstel, alsoo den intrest moet & goeden
evenwel, an gesin nu vastelijcq voor stelt belooft, in 10 a 2 te bett. soo
hebbe mr. Baert Esoght soo lange nogh te pas, alsoo nu aen ul gelosten niet meer
wil twijffelen daer en tussen d. brief bet sijnde, sal ul geerne di now cred. & dienen
aen tet fortiment 't welck ul voor de winter prrov. soude mogen noodigh hebben
waer op moght betrouen ul can selfs overcomen, & tot content ul gerief uyt
soecken, ben seer wel versien van fijn inlanse Coleuren & swarte, oock van Enge &
ranse stesten
Rotterdam wils Hentely
in antwoort aenden ue van 23 deser heb op selvendat p schip
van kappant van hier n aencostij aen toe gesonden 2 cassaes sjd
germerckt een stdwelk p demanie pagkt gelieft te senden aent
mons Jan Loyd en een lasten p selve gaijft te senden aen in Abram
van in london, nemende sehoorlyke reiissen, die aen hun p post
op londen gelieft te sendnen, daelesten aen ueloyd sal ue op hem vergoddn
die ae vivian op mij: des gaght as noch niet garriveet
soo heb het senden vande kann vor dendeodagh teyt gehelt alsoo het sertiemen
niet alvaer dach ueal hope dat oock i tijts saekomen naer over
de oortheyt gelest te hesebaen morgen anderael teanen vori

my last tryon was on the 21m sence recd.y. of 21 & 23d & y easterday the baggh
where in 2 packetts one double M.DV. for m. Michel de vallego, a fingle for mt
Arran Reeves N.11 N, which this day are gou forward I onessingr foos terdemm
letter to m. Souchell shall be sent dun bo marrow, & yd order performed
you have much drapointed mee, not sending some laces, as I lad desired, bearing
so loose the opportuntr, of sending forwaed, which this day I could lave don p post
Pray faile not to send some towards to marrow nnght, for I hoye itt will yet
come in sime by this dayt post, butt pray faile not. I have opened yd stuffs
& shewne them to severall shopkeepers, which lanf att my demandiugh
puses, & daco profter ƒ 14ƒ 16- ƒ 20, & ƒ22- susteed of ƒ13„ 17 „ 25 0ƒ1n
so that I douh I shall tot be able to make, what you exspected
I am inforneed from severall landes, that that com, is shold vere
caep, ji suy offead mee yd answer towards wednes day mormug & I'll
y what I can do some body Hath lewe gord parcell
estamns de lades as ƒ15
Brussel Ant. Bousseau
